%N A396122 Consider the square spiral with its cells numbered starting at 0. Five players take turns and place knights at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing knight of a different player. Sequence lists squares occupied by the first player.
%C A396122 A variant of A392177 with five players.
%H A396122 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A396122/b396122.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396122 Brady Haran, Jonas Karlsson, and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://youtu.be/UiX4CFIiegM">Red & Black Knights (extraordinary result)</a>; <a href="https://youtu.be/VgmDuBCayPw">Amazing Chessboard Patterns (extra)</a>, YouTube Numberphile videos, May 2026
%H A396122 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A396122/a396122.png">Five knights after ten million knights have been placed.</a>
%H A396122 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A396122/a396122.gp.txt">PARI program</a>
